. Standard Contractual Clauses are used to transfer your data to Twilio Inc. to ensure that they are properly protected.
10 - Compliance with laws
Playneta may communicate personal data for the purposes of this Policy to supervisory bodies, judicial authorities, public bodies to which it is mandatory to communicate the data, as well as to those subjects to whom the communication is required by law.
INTERNATIONAL TRANSFER OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
The personal information we collect is stored and/or processed where we or our partners, affiliates, and third-party providers maintain facilities. Please be aware that the locations to which we store, process, or transfer your personal information may not have the same data protection laws as the country in which you initially provided the information. If we transfer your personal information to third parties in other countries: (i) we will perform those transfers in accordance with the requirements of applicable law; and (ii) we will protect the transferred personal information in accordance with this privacy policy.
DATA PROTECTION OFFICER
Data subjects may contact the Data Protection Officer of Playneta with regard to all issues related to processing of their personal data and to the exercise of their rights under data protection law using the following contact details:
Email: privacy@playneta.gg
Postal address: 21 Athanasiou Diakou Street 3032 Limassol, Cyprus
YOUR RIGHTS
Users of our Services have the following rights:
To obtain information regarding the processing of personal data.
To request a copy of their personal data and supplementary information (under the article 15 of GDPR).
To request correction of incorrect, inaccurate, or incomplete personal data (under the article 16 of GDPR).
To request the erasure of personal data when no longer needed or if processing is unlawful (under the article 17 of GDPR).
To request the restriction of the processing of your personal data in certain circumstances (under the article 18 of the GDPR).
To obtain your personal information in a format readable by machines and transfer it to another data controller, a process commonly known as 'data portability' (under the article 20 of GDPR)
To object to the processing of your personal data for marketing purposes or if there are circumstances specific to your situation that warrant such objection (under the article 21 of GDPR).
To withdraw consent for data processing at any time.
To lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (in accordance with Article 77 of the GDPR).
CHILDREN’S PRIVACY
The user must be at least 18 years old to use the Services.
We do not knowingly collect information from children under the age of 18. By providing consent to this Policy, the User certifies that he or she is of sufficient age to give such consent. If we discover that a child under the age of 18 has provided us with his/her personal information, we will delete the information collected. If you are a parent or guardian and you believe that we have collected your child's data in violation of the law, contact us at privacy@playneta.gg. We will delete this data in accordance with applicable law.
LIMITS OF OUR POLICY
Our website may link to external sites that are not operated by us. Please be aware that we have no control over the content and policies of those sites, and cannot accept responsibility or liability for their respective privacy practices.
HOW WE CAN DELETE YOUR DATA
We can delete your data in several cases:
Whenever data is no longer necessary to provide an app experience or service to users (if the user has not accessed the profile for more than 5 years, we assume that the data is no longer needed and delete it)
When requested by a user, as it stated below in this clause,
When a user deletes their account associated with your app,
When it is requested by platform where our app is published,
When required by law or regulation.
You can send a request to retrieve, delete or change your data as follows:
The fastest way to do so is to use the in-game support menu “Contact support”. In the “Personal data request” section you can select an item you are interested in and make a request. In case you have trouble in finding this section, make a general request about the problem, and include “personal data request” in the description. Our Support team uses Zendesk (
Zendesk Privacy Policy
) services to ensure that your request is promptly processed.
Alternatively, you can submit a general request regarding the issue, ensuring to incorporate "Personal data request" in the description, and send it to our email. privacy@playneta.gg.
If you delete a voice message in the chat, it will be immediately removed from our servers and will no longer be accessible. Please note that while the message is deleted from our servers, we cannot control any copies that the recipient may have made using external tools.
COOKIE FILES
We, our marketing partners, analytics service providers use cookies (text files placed on your computer to analyze your use of our Products) and similar technologies (such as pixels, tags and device identifiers) to recognize you and/or your devices and our products and to enhance the products, marketing, analytics or website features we offer. The use of cookies is standard on the Internet.
AMENDMENTS OF THE POLICY
At our discretion, we may change our privacy policy to reflect updates to our business processes, current acceptable practices, or legislative or regulatory changes. If we decide to change this privacy policy, we will post the changes here at the same link by which you are accessing this privacy policy.
LANGUAGE OF THE POLICY
This Policy was originally written in English and may be translated to other languages. In the event of an inconsistency, the English version has the precedence.
CONTACT US
For any questions or concerns regarding your privacy, you may contact us using the following details:
privacy@playneta.gg
Playneta
